# Build context: exclude everything that isn't needed to build the service.
# `turbo prune --docker` only retains the source of the target service in
# `out/full/`, so this list doesn't have to be precise per service.

# Local installs and caches — would be re-installed inside the image anyway.
**/node_modules
**/.pnpm-store
.pnpm-store

# Build outputs — the Dockerfile re-runs `pnpm build` and `pnpm deploy`.
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo
.turbo
out

# Test artifacts
**/coverage
**/.vitest
**/test-results

# Logs
**/*.log
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*
**/pnpm-debug.log*

# Editor / OS junk
**/.vscode
**/.idea
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# Env files (the runtime image gets its env from Kubernetes secrets, not the build context)
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Docker metadata (avoid recursion)
**/Dockerfile
**/docker-compose*.yml
**/.dockerignore

# Git
**/.git
**/.gitignore
**/.gitattributes

# Documentation
**/*.md
**/README*
**/CHANGELOG*
**/LICENSE*
**/.github

# Per-service generated/cloned artifacts
**/.husky/_/husky.sh
**/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
